    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The Lovelace textbook connects RL to dopamine reward prediction errors in the brain, which is one of computational cognitive science's strongest success stories. This page focuses on the algorithms: bandits, TD learning, and Q-learning. The textbook also covers policy gradient methods and model-based RL, which connect to the planning and decision-making material in Chapter 6.</p>

